# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public keys (safe to expose to the browser). Found in:
#   Supabase Dashboard -> Project Settings -> API
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Server-only key. NEVER expose this to the browser or commit it.
# Used by server actions / API routes to write leads and scan data.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google PageSpeed Insights (Website Performance scanner)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional but recommended. The scanner works without a key but is heavily rate
# limited; with a key it is reliable. Create one in Google Cloud Console
# (enable the "PageSpeed Insights API"). When unset, the Website Performance
# category falls back to deterministic placeholder scoring.
# GOOGLE_PAGESPEED_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DataForSEO (Local SEO + Reputation scanner — Google Business Profile data)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional. When set, the Local SEO and Reputation categories use real Google
# Business Profile data (rating, review count, profile completeness). Without
# these, both categories fall back to deterministic placeholder scoring.
# Credentials come from your DataForSEO dashboard (API access).
# DATAFORSEO_LOGIN=
# DATAFORSEO_PASSWORD=
# Optional. DataForSEO needs a *recognized* location to resolve a single Google
# business panel. By default the app resolves each lead's typed city to a
# DataForSEO location_code automatically (via the locations list below), so no
# configuration is needed — leads from any US city are handled. Overrides:
#   - DATAFORSEO_LOCATION: force a fixed location NAME for every scan, e.g.
#     "Miami,Florida,United States". Wins over per-lead resolution.
#   - DATAFORSEO_LOCATION_CODE: the country-wide fallback code used when a
#     city can't be resolved (default 2840 = United States).
#   - DATAFORSEO_LOCATIONS_ENDPOINT: the locations list used for per-lead
#     resolution (default the DataForSEO US SERP locations endpoint; codes are
#     unified across Google endpoints).
# DATAFORSEO_LOCATION=
# DATAFORSEO_LOCATION_CODE=2840
# DATAFORSEO_LOCATIONS_ENDPOINT=
# When the exact-name lookup is ambiguous (e.g. two same-named restaurants in a
# city), the scanner falls back to a business-listings search scoped to the
# metro and picks the listing whose website matches the lead's — these tune it:
#   - DATAFORSEO_LISTINGS_ENDPOINT: the search endpoint (default the DataForSEO
#     business listings search/live endpoint).
#   - DATAFORSEO_SEARCH_RADIUS_KM: metro radius around the city (default 30).
# DATAFORSEO_LISTINGS_ENDPOINT=
# DATAFORSEO_SEARCH_RADIUS_KM=30

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Geocoding (city -> coordinates for the business-listings fallback search)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional. The DataForSEO listings fallback needs a lat/lng to scope the search
# to the right metro. Defaults to OpenStreetMap Nominatim (no API key, fine for
# low volume). For higher volume, point GEOCODE_ENDPOINT at a keyed provider.
# Set a descriptive GEOCODE_USER_AGENT per Nominatim's usage policy.
# GEOCODE_ENDPOINT=
# GEOCODE_USER_AGENT=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Claude API (AI-generated recommendations)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional. When set, the "Top 5 recommendations" are generated by Claude from
# the real scan findings (specific to the restaurant) instead of static
# templates. Get a key from the Anthropic Console. Model is overridable via
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL (defaults to claude-opus-4-8).
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Trigger.dev (run scans as background jobs)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional, and requires Supabase. When set, form submissions enqueue the scan
# as a background job (off the request path) and the results page polls Supabase
# for the result. When unset, scans run inline in the /api/scan route.
#   - TRIGGER_SECRET_KEY: from the Trigger.dev dashboard (used by the app to
#     enqueue jobs). Deploy the tasks with `npx trigger.dev@latest deploy`.
#   - TRIGGER_PROJECT_REF: your project ref (also set in trigger.config.ts).
#   - TRIGGER_API_URL: only for self-hosted Trigger.dev.
# The task's own runtime env (Supabase/PageSpeed/DataForSEO/Anthropic keys) is
# configured in the Trigger.dev dashboard, not here.
# TRIGGER_SECRET_KEY=
# TRIGGER_PROJECT_REF=
# TRIGGER_API_URL=
